Now, to solve the number of miles to drive per year before you make the decision, we can use this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Number of miles}&=\dfrac{\text{Total additional cost}}{\text{Difference in fuel consumption}}
\end{aligned}$$ 

This allows us to solve for the break-even value of the project.

Substituting the known values, we will get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Number of miles}&=\dfrac{\$7,600}{\$0.0219}\\[15 pt]
&=347,031.96\ \text{miles}
\end{aligned}$$
